## 26R1 vs 25R2 Diff — Confirmed Results

### New Fields in 26R1

| Table | Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|-------|------|-------|
| INSiteStatus | QtyMLPrepared | decimal(25,6) | Manufacturing/Logistics qty prepared — backed by INSiteStatusByCostCenter |
| INSiteStatus | QtyMLBooked | decimal(25,6) | ML qty booked |
| INSiteStatus | QtyMLDispatched | decimal(25,6) | ML qty dispatched |
| INSiteStatus | QtyMLAllocated | decimal(25,6) | ML qty allocated — only populated on Manufacturing-enabled tenants |
| InventoryItem | SOSource | char(1) | Source for SO line PO behavior. 'N'=None, 'D'=Drop-Ship, 'O'=Purchase to Order. Only shown when Drop-Shipments or SO-to-PO Link feature is enabled. Physical column — do NOT use in SQL views targeting 25R1 or 25R2. |
| INTran | IsUnassigned | bit | Internal flag (PXDBBool, default false). No reporting value. Safe to ignore in SQL views. |

### Confirmed Unchanged vs 25R2

| Table | Status |
|-------|--------|
| INItemSite | PXProjection structure identical — still joins INItemSite + INSite + INItemStats |
| INItemSite.LastCost | Still PXDBPriceCost(BqlField = typeof(INItemStats.lastCost)) |
| INItemSite.MinQty | Still labeled "Reorder Point" in UI |
| INPIDetail.SiteID | Still a proper FK field |
| INTran.DocType / TranType | Both physical columns, both present, IsKey structure unchanged |
| INSiteStatus PK | Still (InventoryID, SubItemID, SiteID) — pre-aggregation still required |
| ARRegister | 155 fields — unchanged. Line delta is C# primary constructor syntax refactoring only. |
| APRegister | Same — syntax refactoring only, no field changes |

## Cross-Version SQL Safety

Fields safe on ALL versions (25R1, 25R2, 26R1): all fields documented in dac-table-map.md without a version tag.

Fields safe on 25R2 and 26R1 only:
- dbo.INItemStats.LastCost (table introduced in 25R2)

Fields safe on 26R1 only (do NOT use in SQL targeting 25R1 or 25R2):
- dbo.InventoryItem.SOSource
- dbo.INSiteStatus.QtyMLPrepared / QtyMLBooked / QtyMLDispatched / QtyMLAllocated
- dbo.INTran.IsUnassigned